         <abstract>
            <p>In the last few months, inflation, high interest rates, and then recession have assaulted banks in quick succession. Highly publicized difficulties of a few institutions have focused considerable attention on the activities and management of banks and bank holding companies. In light of these events, this article discusses the application of financial management in commercial banks and bank holding companies.</p>
         </abstract>
